{"code":1,"isDone":false,"toInsertArticleList":[{"createdTime":"2020-09-05 16:56:47","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:56:47","title":"2020 Malaysian Superbike Championship calendar released – 2 rounds in Sept and Oct, possible 6 races","link":"https://paultan.org/?p=1171898","description":"<p><a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/2020-malaysian-superbike-championship-calendar-released-2-rounds-in-sept-and-oct-possible-6-races/2020-malaysian-superbike-championship-2/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1171989\"><img src=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/2020-Malaysian-Superbike-Championship-2-630x419.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"630\" height=\"419\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1171989\" srcset=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/2020-Malaysian-Superbike-Championship-2-630x419.jpg 630w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/2020-Malaysian-Superbike-Championship-2-1200x799.jpg 1200w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/2020-Malaysian-Superbike-Championship-2-850x566.jpg 850w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Constraints and limitations imposed by the Covid-19 pandemic and Revised Movement Control Order have curtailed motorsports in Malaysia but the Malaysian Superbike Championship (MSBK) will go on. A severely curtailed racing calendar for this year will now have two rounds instead of the previously proposed four.</p>\n<p>However, instead of only two races per round, there are plans to hold three races instead. This is possible if the number of race days per round is increased. Both rounds will be held at Sepang International Circuit with the first event taking place September 25 to 27 followed by the second round from October 16 to 18.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/2020-malaysian-superbike-championship-calendar-released-2-rounds-in-sept-and-oct-possible-6-races/2020-malaysian-superbike-championship-1/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1171987\"><img src=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/2020-Malaysian-Superbike-Championship-1-630x419.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"630\" height=\"419\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1171987\" srcset=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/2020-Malaysian-Superbike-Championship-1-630x419.jpg 630w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/2020-Malaysian-Superbike-Championship-1-1200x799.jpg 1200w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/2020-Malaysian-Superbike-Championship-1-850x566.jpg 850w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" /></a></p>\n<p>As a national championship, MSBK is a local professional motorcycle race series and provides a platform to groom and develop Malaysian talents and teams. New for this year is the MSBK150, to run on specifications similar to the regional Asian Road Racing Championship.</p>\n<p>Differentiated from the Malaysian Cub Prix CP150 class which is reserved for elite teams, the MSBK150 is open to all teams and riders. With the inclusion of MSBK150, the MSBK championship now includes motorcycle racing for 150, 250, 600 and 1,000 cc racing machines.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/2020-malaysian-superbike-championship-calendar-released-2-rounds-in-sept-and-oct-possible-6-races/\">2020 Malaysian Superbike Championship calendar released 16:56:47","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:56:47","title":"September 2020 week two fuel price – RON 95 down to RM1.71, RON 97 to RM2.01, diesel prices unchanged","link":"https://paultan.org/?p=1172060","description":"<p><a href=\"https://paultan.org/2017/06/21/june-2017-week-four-fuel-prices-petrol-goes-down/petrol-diesel-ron95-ron97-fuel-pump/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-675507\"><img src=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2017/06/petrol-diesel-ron95-ron97-fuel-pump-630x429.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"630\" height=\"429\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-675507\" srcset=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2017/06/petrol-diesel-ron95-ron97-fuel-pump-630x429.jpg 630w, sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" /></a></p>\n<p>It&#8217;s Friday, which means it is also time for the weekly fuel price update, and a little joy for petrol users. The coming week of September 5 until September 11 will see a one sen drop for RON 95 and RON 97 petrols, while diesel prices are unchanged from last week. </p>\n<p>According to the ministry of finance, Euro 4M RON 95 petrol will be priced at RM1.71 per litre, down from RM1.72 <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/08/28/september-2020-week-one-fuel-price-ron-95-up-to-rm1-72-ron-97-to-rm2-02-diesel-down-to-rm1-78/\">last week</a>. Meanwhile, RON 97 petrol sees an adjustment to RM2.01 per litre, down from RM2.02 last week. </p>\n<p>For Euro 2M diesel, this fuel will remain unchanged in price from RM1.78 last week. Correspondingly, Euro 5 diesel will be 10 sen dearer, also holding station at RM1.88 from last week. </p>\n<p>These prices will remain in effect until September 11, when the next round of fuel prices will be announced. This is the 35th edition of the <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2018/12/24/ron-95-petrol-weekly-float-to-start-from-jan-1-2019/\">weekly fuel pricing format</a> for this year and the 87th in total for the format, running from midnight on Saturday until the following Friday. </p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/september-2020-week-two-fuel-price-ron-95-down-to-rm1-71-ron-97-to-rm2-01-diesel-prices-unchanged/\">September 2020 week two fuel price &#8211; RON 95 down to RM1.71, RON 97 to RM2.01, diesel prices unchanged</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://paultan.org\">Paul Tan&#039;s Automotive News</a>.</p>\n","descriptionType":"html","publishedDate":"Fri, 04 Sep 2020 09:23:11 +0000","feedId":13729,"bgimg":"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2017/06/petrol-diesel-ron95-ron97-fuel-pump-108x108.jpg","linkMd5":"0b7b506491b40cd031c4b9e5cc6064f2","bgimgJsdelivr":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx7/cdn24@2020_1/2020/09/05/08-57-21-052_b1f0b3e38596e215.webp","destWidth":108,"destHeight":108,"sourceBytes":7568,"destBytes":3036,"author":"Mick Chan","enclosureType":"image/jpeg","enclosureUrl":"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2017/06/petrol-diesel-ron95-ron97-fuel-pump-108x108.jpg","articleImgCdnMap":{"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2017/06/petrol-diesel-ron95-ron97-fuel-pump-630x429.jpg":null},"publishedOrCreatedDate":1599296207021},{"createdTime":"2020-09-05 16:56:47","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:56:47","title":"Merdeka Race 2020 – SIC Viper Niza wins MSF Ultimate category; Wenso Racing Team scores three class wins","link":"https://paultan.org/?p=1171727","description":"<p><a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/merdeka-race-2020-sic-viper-niza-wins-msf-ultimate-category-wenso-racing-team-scores-three-class-wins/msf-merdeka-2020-2/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1171964\"><img src=\"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-2-630x420.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"630\" height=\"420\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1171964\" srcset=\"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-2-630x420.jpg 630w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-2-1200x800.jpg 1200w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-2-850x567.jpg 850w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-2.jpg 1500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" /></a></p>\n<p>The celebration of National Day in Malaysia has, in recent years, also come to be a time of endurance racing, and this year&#8217;s closed-door function played host to the <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/08/28/merdeka-race-2020-happens-this-weekend-watch-msf-enduro-mcs-live-on-fb-astro-delayed-telecast/\">Merdeka Race 2020</a> that was a joint two-day event by the Malaysia Speed Festival (MSF) and Sepang International Circuit (SIC). This was a special round that combined two of the country&#8217;s top production car racing series, with more than 200 race cars in participation.</p>\n<p>In the MSF series, all race cars are sponsored and <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/08/26/petron-is-the-official-fuel-partner-for-msf-merdeka-enduro-race-to-provide-its-blaze100-fuel-to-all-racers/\">fuelled by Petron Blaze100 RON 100 petrol</a>, and ran on Hankook RS4 and Hankook Z221 control tyres. </p>\n<p>The first race of the weekend saw Hazrin Mad Kaidi driving the Toyota Corolla Levin AE111 of JMS Tuner Team take the battle all the way to the end of the race. Kenny Lee in the Toyota Corolla Levin AE111 of Kegani Racing Team contested for position with BP Chu and Ahmad Ridhwan&#8217;s Honda Civic EG6 of Acanta Racing Team early in the race.</p>\n<p>However, fuel surge issues for the EG6 in the last two laps of the race meant Hazrin could through just in time for the race win. Kenny Lee led early in the race, however he was handed a time penalty for a pit lane infringement during the compulsory three-minute pitstop.</p>\n\n<a href='https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/merdeka-race-2020-sic-viper-niza-wins-msf-ultimate-category-wenso-racing-team-scores-three-class-wins/msf-merdeka-2020-14/'><img width=\"108\" height=\"108\" src=\"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-14-108x108.jpg\" class=\"attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-14-108x108.jpg 108w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-14-70x70.jpg 70w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-14-80x80.jpg 80w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-14-160x160.jpg 160w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-14-216x216.jpg 216w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 108px) 100vw, 108px\" /></a>\n<a href='https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/merdeka-race-2020-sic-viper-niza-wins-msf-ultimate-category-wenso-racing-team-scores-three-class-wins/msf-merdeka-2020-8/'><img width=\"108\" height=\"108\" src=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-8-108x108.jpg\" class=\"attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-8-108x108.jpg 108w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-8-70x70.jpg 70w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-8-80x80.jpg 80w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-8-160x160.jpg 160w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-8-216x216.jpg 216w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 108px) 100vw, 108px\" /></a>\n\n<p>Meanwhile in the Street 2000 category, defending class champion Fahrizal Hassan in the Toyota GT86 of RBM Motorsport contested against the hard-charging Honda Civic EG9 of Millenium Motorsports Asia piloted by Faisal Naim and Akina Teo, who emerged in the race lead after pit stops and carried on to take the win. </p>\n<p>There was plenty of excitement to spare in the Saga Cup category. Two 45-minute segments were split by a 10-minute turnaround break for one-and-a-half hour of race time, during which plenty of drama took place; the heat of competition saw the demise of wheel hubs, a race car catching fire on the back straight, while another rolled over at the off-camber Turn 11. However, as testament to the safety equipment and regulations in place, all drivers involved emerged unscathed. </p>\n<p>Ahmad Tarmimi Tahang lead early on, though his car succumbed to engine failure half an hour into the race, handing the race lead over to Shafiq Shaiful, who was closely followed by Daniel Chan of Loon Power who gave chase right to the halfway mark. At the start of Heat 2 after the 10-minute turnaround break, Daniel Chan made his move around the outside of Shafiq&#8217;s second driver, Hafiz Bachok for the race lead.</p>\n<p>Daniel would lead the five-car pack battling for first position, and remained in control of the race until a leaking fuel cap saw him run out of fuel before the finish was in sight, eventually coming to a halt at Turn 11. The duo of Hafiz Bachok and Shafiq Shaiful of Malkar Racing Team took the race win, ahead of Tan Chaw Wei, and M Noor Rahim and Shaiful Zamri.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/merdeka-race-2020-sic-viper-niza-wins-msf-ultimate-category-wenso-racing-team-scores-three-class-wins/msf-merdeka-2020-7/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1171961\"><img src=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-7-630x420.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"630\" height=\"420\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1171961\" srcset=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-7-630x420.jpg 630w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-7-1200x800.jpg 1200w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-7-850x567.jpg 850w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-7.jpg 1500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" /></a></p>\n<p>The on-track excitement continued on Sunday in the Super Street and Ultimate categories. Super Street category pole position starter Kevin Kumar and the Mitsubishi Lancer Evolution X of Millenium Motorsports Asia led early in the race, but dramatically left the circuit at the high-speed Turn 6, narrowly missing the Proton Satria of SPV-Ravenol Racing Team and the FD2 Honda Civic Type R of Wenso Racing Team. </p>\n<p>The Super Street race start was also followed shortly thereafter by another turbo casualty, with the Proton Inspira 4WD Turbo of EXN-JR SuciMuci Racing Team having started from second on the grid. This almost immediately faced issues right after the start, as the car experienced a loss of boost on Lap 1, eventually arriving back in the pits to retire after just two laps. The culprit was a turbo hose that had melted. </p>\n<p>The two turbo 4WD retirements cleared the route for Desmond Yee of N1 Racing Team, who took the race lead in his DC5 Honda Integra Type R. A hard-charging Calvin Wong of Wenso Racing Team in the FD2 Civic Type R took the lead thereafter. </p>\n<p>Though Desmond looked like he was mounting a challenge from second place after the compulsory pit stop, Wenso Racing Team&#8217;s second driver Shahrin Kamaruzzam maintained a two- to three-second gap until the end to take the race win. Gavin Mun in the DC5 Honda Integra Type R of Millenium Motorsports Asia completed the Super Street podium.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/merdeka-race-2020-sic-viper-niza-wins-msf-ultimate-category-wenso-racing-team-scores-three-class-wins/msf-merdeka-2020-11/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1171969\"><img src=\"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-11-630x421.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"630\" height=\"421\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1171969\" srcset=\"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-11-630x421.jpg 630w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-11-1200x801.jpg 1200w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-11-850x567.jpg 850w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-11.jpg 1498w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" /></a></p>\n<p>A three-way battle ensued in the MSF Ultimate category on Sunday night, where the locally-built Honda EG6 Civic duo were set to take on the SEAT Leon Cupra TCR of Team SIC Viper Niza. The Civic fielded by Fawster 22 ProShop featured a turbocharged 1.8 litre B-series engine, while the Team FAST Autoworks entry was powered by a 2.4 litre K-series unit. </p>\n<p>As for the Cupra TCR, this was the same car that Douglas Khoo, Dominique Ang, Melvin Moh, and Fariqe Hairuman took to the Pro-Am class win at last year&#8217;s TCR Spa 500. At the MSF Ultimate race start, the Team FAST Autoworks Civic got the jump on the SEAT, while the Faidzil Alang-piloted Civic of Fawster 22 ProShop got the better of the field and entered Turn 1 in the lead. </p>\n<p>Just two seconds covered the top three cars in the first four laps, although Pee Sau Peng of Team FAST Autoworks fell back from the lead pack from Lap 5. The Cupra TCR driven by Adam Khalid kept pace with Faidzil in his Fawster 22 ProShop Civic, both cars in the lead pack lapping consistently in the 2-minute 21-second region. </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/merdeka-race-2020-sic-viper-niza-wins-msf-ultimate-category-wenso-racing-team-scores-three-class-wins/msf-merdeka-2020-10/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1171965\"><img src=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-10-630x420.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"630\" height=\"420\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1171965\" srcset=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-10-630x420.jpg 630w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-10-1200x799.jpg 1200w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-10-850x566.jpg 850w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-10.jpg 1500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" /></a></p>\n<p>It was not to be for the turbocharged blue Civic, however, as gearbox troubles forced it to yield the race lead to the Team SIC Viper Niza racer. Early lead pack contender Pee Sau Peng also had to fold, having to pit early and the team&#8217;s crew scrambling to cool the car. This game of attrition saw the FD2 Civic Type R of Wenso Racing Team bump up to second place, driven by 2019 Ultimate class champion Azlan Malik and Muner Jihan.</p>\n<p>Team SIC Viper Niza went into the 10-minute turnaround break with a one-lap lead, and resumed in Heat 2 with Gilbert Ang now at the wheel, subsequently leading the race until the finish for the overall race win and the honours for the Ultimate category. Azlan Malik and Muner Jihan of the Wenso Racing Team took second overall, and the Ultimate Touring class win. </p>\n<p>Wenso Racing Team emerged from the Merdeka Race 2020 with three wins in total, with the aforementioned Ultimate Touring win, Amirul Hafiz and Azlan Malik in the same car with the Touring Production title in Race 2 of the Malaysia Championship Series, plus Calvin Wong and Shahrin Kamaruzzam in MSF Super Street with the FD2 Civic Type R. </p>\n\n<a b2.webp","http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-6-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx12/cdn97@2020_5/2020/09/05/08-56-50-592_b8db5338eee9172c.webp","http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-3-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx3/cdn57@2020_4/2020/09/05/08-57-00-996_edc3c86b0cc4c5c9.webp","http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-4-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx12/cdn25@2020_3/2020/09/05/08-56-53-089_5a11ce0ad3d56d42.webp","http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/MSF-Merdeka-2020-5-108x108.jpg":null},"publishedOrCreatedDate":1599296207022},{"createdTime":"2020-09-05 16:56:47","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:56:47","title":"VIDEO: Honda City RS i-MMD hybrid – style matters","link":"https://paultan.org/?p=1171628","description":"<p><iframe src=\"https://www.facebook.com/plugins/video.php?href=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fhondamalaysia%2Fvideos%2F342293737136513%2F&#038;show_text=false&#038;width=735&#038;height=412&#038;appId\" width=\"735\" height=\"412\" style=\"border:none;overflow:hidden\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"0\" allowTransparency=\"true\" allow=\"encrypted-media\" allowFullScreen=\"true\"></iframe></p>\n<p>The Malaysian B-segment car market is about to heat up real good, with <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/spyshot-proton-iriz-crossover-dan-persona-facelift-2021-dikesan-sedang-diuji-guna-kotak-gear-4at/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">new offerings from Proton</a>, <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/09/01/nissan-almera-to-debut-new-brand-logo-in-malaysia/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Nissan</a>, and Honda being right around the corner. Just earlier today, Honda Malaysia released its second video advertisement featuring the hotly anticipated <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/08/24/gallery-2020-honda-city-rs-i-mmd-malaysia-to-get-honda-sensing-lanewatch-and-rear-disc-brakes/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Honda City RS i-MMD Hybrid</a>, with a brief cameo of its perennial rival, the <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2019/02/21/driven-2019-toyota-vios-old-hand-learns-new-tricks/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Toyota Vios</a>. But of course.</p>\n<p>Compared to the <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/08/14/video-2020-honda-city-rs-i-mmd-hybrid-ad-takes-a-swipe-at-toyota-vios-camry-and-perodua-bezza/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">previous &#8220;Torque Matters&#8221; video theme</a>, the second installment is a lot more focused on the City RS itself. The video highlighted features such as the gloss black front grille, fog light garnish, black side mirror caps, dual-tone alloy wheels, rear diffuser and the black rear spoiler. </p>\n<p>Aside from the video, the Malaysian City RS, notably the e:HEV RS variant, will be equipped with Honda&#8217;s Intelligent Multi-Mode Drive (i-MMD) hybrid system, equipped with twin electric motors. The most powerful of these motors makes the headlining 109 PS and 253 Nm of torque and drives the car most of the time, while the 98 PS/127 Nm 1.5 litre petrol engine acts as a generator and provides direct drive at higher speeds, where it is most efficient.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;re expecting the RS to be joined by the usual S, E and V variants, although those are tipped to be powered by a new, non-electrified twin-cam (DOHC) 1.5 litre naturally-aspirated i-VTEC mill. In India, this engine makes 121 PS and 145 Nm, and is paired to a CVT. Honda Sensing will likely debut on the fifth-gen City as well, although the extent of which remains uncertain. Watch our walk-around video, below.</p>\n<p><iframe width=\"630\" height=\"354\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Iaw58NV7u9A?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; -53-259_d7704bd646238e57.webp","http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/08/2020-Honda-City-RS-Preview-24-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx5oss/cdn3@2020_6/2020/09/05/08-57-01-615_d9ce11264cd3d8d4.webp","http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/08/2020-Honda-City-RS-Preview-25-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx32/cdn54@2020_2/2020/09/05/08-56-59-722_d7b6f797b4777985.webp"},"publishedOrCreatedDate":1599296207024},{"createdTime":"2020-09-05 SUV","link":"https://paultan.org/?p=1171706","description":"<p><a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/hyundai-sonata-eighth-gen-spotted-in-kona-teaser-shot-hinting-at-malaysian-introduction-after-the-suv/hyundai-sonata-dn8-teaser/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1171888\"><img src=\"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Hyundai-Sonata-DN8-teaser-630x419.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"630\" height=\"419\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1171888\" http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Hyundai-Sonata-DN8-teaser-850x565.jpg 850w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" /></a></p>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2017/06/13/hyundai-kona-compact-suv-for-millennials-revealed/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Hyundai Kona</a>, which will be making its Malaysian market debut in the <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/08/27/hyundai-kona-malaysian-debut-in-q4-cbu-fr-rm11xk/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">next couple of months</a>, has again been teased on a <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/hyundaimalaysia/photos/a.133946836662995/3286093658114948/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">post on the Hyundai Malaysia Facebook page</a>, but the upcoming SUV isn&#8217;t the highlight piece in the shot &#8211; rather, the car in the background is, and we&#8217;re not talking about the <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2019/11/28/hyundai-i30-n-launched-in-malaysia-20-units-only-available-on-lazada-during-12-12-grand-sale-rm299k/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">i30 N</a>.</p>\n<p>The car conveniently placed within the frame happens to be the new <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2019/04/18/2020-hyundai-sonata-eighth-gen-model-debuts-in-ny/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">eighth-generation Sonata</a>, suggesting that the sedan may be the next model to be introduced locally after the Kona, although exactly when remains to be seen. It will take over from the <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2014/12/09/hyundai-sonata-lf-launched-in-malaysia/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">seventh-gen LF</a>, which was <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2018/04/17/new-hyundai-santa-fe-sonata-planned-for-malaysia-current-gen-models-including-veloster-phased-out/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">phased out locally in 2018</a>.</p>\n<p>The new DN8, unveiled in <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2019/03/06/2020-hyundai-sonata-revealed-with-coupe-like-styling/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">March last year</a>, adopts a new four-door coupe styling direction with plenty of design cues from the <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2018/03/08/hyundai-le-fil-rouge-reveals-new-design-language/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Le Fil Rouge (HDC-1) concept</a>, and the sportback flow of the rear end is shown to great effect in the Kona teaser image.</p>\n\n<a href='https://paultan.org/2019/04/18/2020-hyundai-sonata-eighth-gen-model-debuts-in-ny/2020-hyundai-sonata-39/'><img width=\"108\" height=\"108\" http://s1.paultan.org/image/2019/04/2020-Hyundai-Sonata-3-216x216.jpg 216w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 108px) 100vw, 108px\" /></a>\n\n<p>The fresh exterior isn&#8217;t the only thing buyers will have to look forward to, because the Sonata&#8217;s interior has also been overhauled. A new dashboard layout, which is dressed with a 10.25-inch infotainment touchscreen and a 12.3-inch digital instrument cluster, are among the visual highlights in the breezy, modern-looking cabin.</p>\n<p>Nothing is yet known about the specifications of the local model, but there&#8217;s plenty of kit and options available for the sedan in global markets, and these include items such as a Bose Premium sound system, sunroof as well as ventilated front seats.</p>\n\n<a href='https://paultan.org/2019/04/18/2020-hyundai-sonata-eighth-gen-model-debuts-in-ny/2020-hyundai-sonata-48/'><img automaker&#8217;s SmartSense suite of advanced driver assistance systems, which includes items such as advanced smart cruise control with stop and go, forward collision avoidance assist (AEB), blind-spot collision warning and lane keeping assist in its kitbag. With the Kona set to come equipped with SmartSense, the suite should be a given on the Sonata.</p>\n<p>The powertrain for the local model also remains unknown. Global options include a series of Smartstream units ranging from a 2.5 litre naturally-aspirated GDI engine with 191 hp and 245 Nm to a 1.6 litre turbocharged GDI unit offering 180 hp and 264 Nm, both paired with an eight-speed automatic transmission. There are also 2.0 litre MPI petrol and GDI <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2019/07/24/2020-hyundai-sonata-hybrid-debuts-solar-panel-roof/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">hybrid</a> /05/08-56-54-755_80be3b6ccf575648.webp","http://s1.paultan.org/image/2019/04/2020-Hyundai-Sonata-24-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx8/cdn83@2020_3/2020/09/05/08-57-02-809_b5bf5f9d01307069.webp","http://s3.paultan.org/image/2019/04/2020-Hyundai-Sonata-25-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx8/cdn91@2020_1/2020/09/05/08-56-54-618_4c2e71e05971885d.webp","http://s3.paultan.org/image/2019/04/2020-Hyundai-Sonata-26-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx27/cdn10@2020_5/2020/09/05/08-56-54-800_002a19daa6499f86.webp","http://s1.paultan.org/image/2019/04/2020-Hyundai-Sonata-27-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx12/cdn15@2020_5/2020/09/05/08-57-00-526_1b99d0a40ceaafdb.webp","http://s3.paultan.org/image/2019/04/2020-Hyundai-Sonata-28-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx24/cdn14@2020_1/2020/09/05/08-56-53-656_1a8a43c059fba65d.webp","http://s1.paultan.org/image/2019/04/2020-Hyundai-Sonata-29-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx13/cdn94@2020_4/2020/09/05/08-56-56-914_51c1ace769bdfe55.webp","http://s1.paultan.org/image/2019/04/2020-Hyundai-Sonata-30-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx27/cdn88@2020_2/2020/09/05/08-57-01-399_a41c752ad7019f84.webp","http://s3.paultan.org/image/2019/04/2020-Hyundai-Sonata-31-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx6/cdn85@2020_5/2020/09/05/08-56-53-587_cd7493becef19810.webp","http://s3.paultan.org/image/2019/04/2020-Hyundai-Sonata-32-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx8/cdn3@2020_1/2020/09/05/08-56-55-859_d37d98b36648aed2.webp","http://s1.paultan.org/image/2019/04/2020-Hyundai-Sonata-33-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx12/cdn89@2020_2/2020/09/05/08-56-57-712_34b74091ad8d3819.webp","http://s1.paultan.org/image/2019/04/2020-Hyundai-Sonata-34-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx30/cdn50@2020_6/2020/09/05/08-56-53-231_9ef4bff0f495e342.webp","http://s3.paultan.org/image/2019/04/2020-Hyundai-Sonata-35-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx1/cdn40@2020_1/2020/09/05/08-57-01-984_b59523010b95cb99.webp"},"publishedOrCreatedDate":1599296207023},{"createdTime":"2020-09-05 16:56:47","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:56:47","title":"GMA T.50s announced – hardcore 890 kg track beast, 3.9L NA V12 with 730 PS; 25 units only, from RM17 mil","link":"https://paultan.org/?p=1171383","description":"<p><a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/gma-t-50s-announced-hardcore-890-kg-track-beast-3-9l-na-v12-with-730-ps-25-units-only-from-rm17-mil/gordonmurrayautomotivet-50s_8mb/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1171390\"><img src=\"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/GordonMurrayAutomotiveT.50s_8MB-630x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"630\" height=\"220\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1171390\" srcset=\"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/GordonMurrayAutomotiveT.50s_8MB-630x220.jpg 630w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/GordonMurrayAutomotiveT.50s_8MB-1200x420.jpg 1200w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/GordonMurrayAutomotiveT.50s_8MB-850x297.jpg 850w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Just a month after revealing the <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/08/05/gma-t-50-debuts-true-mclaren-f1-successor-with-3-9l-na-v12-12100-rpm-redline-986-kg-rm13-million/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">T.50</a>, Gordon Murray Automotive (GMA) announced the more hardcore, track-focused T.50s supercar. This one will be made in even smaller numbers &#8211; 25 units only, but expect them to be snapped up just as quickly as the regular T.50 did. </p>\n<p>In case you didn&#8217;t know, the T.50 has a starting price of RM13 million, but all 100 units were sold within 48 hours of its unveiling. If you missed the boat and still want to get your hands on the <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2017/01/27/mclaren-f1-the-story-behind-its-record-top-speed/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">McLaren F1</a> successor, then this T.50s is all that&#8217;s left. Just be prepared to part with at least £3.1 million (RM17 million). Be quick, though, because half of the allocation has already been spoken for.</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s kick things off where it matters &#8211; performance. The T.50s is powered by the same <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/08/13/gma-t-50s-bespoke-3-9l-na-v8-by-cosworth-detailed/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Cosworth-made, 3.9 litre naturally-aspirated V12 engine</a>, but gets completely reworked for maximum performance. Here, the engine puts out over 700 PS through completely revised cylinder heads and camshafts, a higher compression ratio, plus an all-new free flow exhaust system. </p>\n<p>The periscope-style roof-mounted ram-air inlet (replete with an aero fin) on the regular T.50 has also been modified, contributing to an additional 30 PS. An entirely new, bespoke six-speed IGS (Instantaneous Gearchange System) gearbox by Xtrac is used here, replacing the T.50&#8217;s manual gearbox. </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/08/05/gma-t-50-debuts-true-mclaren-f1-successor-with-3-9l-na-v12-12100-rpm-redline-986-kg-rm13-million/2021-gordon-murray-automotive-t-50-supercar-engine-4/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1155298\"><img src=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/08/2021-Gordon-Murray-Automotive-T.50-Supercar-Engine-4-e1597309736702-630x329.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"630\" height=\"329\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1155298\" srcset=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/08/2021-Gordon-Murray-Automotive-T.50-Supercar-Engine-4-e1597309736702-630x329.jpg 630w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/08/2021-Gordon-Murray-Automotive-T.50-Supercar-Engine-4-e1597309736702-1200x627.jpg 1200w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/08/2021-Gordon-Murray-Automotive-T.50-Supercar-Engine-4-e1597309736702-850x444.jpg 850w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" /></a></p>\n<p>No performance figures have been revealed yet, but expect GMA engineers to surpass every threshold of the Cosworth mill. Just as a reminder, the road-going tune gets a rev ceiling of 12,100 rpm, and boasts a ridiculously quick 28,400 pick-up revs per second. It claims to be the most responsive road-legal engine to be made, taking just 0.3 seconds for the engine to hit its redline from idle. We&#8217;re still in awe.</p>\n<p>To make sure all that power gets properly channeled onto the road, the team installed a 1,758 mm-wide delta wing (a nod to Murray&#8217;s 1983 Brabham BT52 Formula One car), which works in tandem with the underbody aerofoil, front splitter, adjustable diffusers, and the car’s 400 mm fan. All these help generate in excess of 1,500 kg of downforce, or 170% of the car’s 890 kg total weight.</p>\n<p>Compared to the road car with six aerodynamic profiles, the T.50s operates in High Downforce Mode at all times, with the underbody diffusor ducts fully open and the fan running permanently at 7,000 rpm. GMA says the car is able to generate around 2.5G to 3Gs of force under braking with the aerodynamic package. At 280 km/h, the T.50s creates enough downforce for it to drive upside down.</p>\n<p>For suspension, it uses the same rising rate suspension as the T.50, but the spring rates, dampers and front anti-roll bar have been uprated for racing. Ride height has been dropped 40 mm front and rear, and the oil coolers have been moved to the sides of the car for better airflow. Michelin Cup Sport 2 tyres are fitted onto the lightweight forged magnesium wheels.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/08/05/gma-t-50-debuts-true-mclaren-f1-successor-with-3-9l-na-v12-12100-rpm-redline-986-kg-rm13-million/2021-gordon-murray-automotive-t-50-supercar-exterior-5/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1155303\"><img src=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/08/2021-Gordon-Murray-Automotive-T.50-Supercar-Exterior-4-630x330.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"630\" height=\"330\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1155303\" srcset=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/08/2021-Gordon-Murray-Automotive-T.50-Supercar-Exterior-4-630x330.jpg 630w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/08/2021-Gordon-Murray-Automotive-T.50-Supercar-Exterior-4-1200x628.jpg 1200w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/08/2021-Gordon-Murray-Automotive-T.50-Supercar-Exterior-4-850x445.jpg 850w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Meanwhile, stopping power is provided by Brembo carbon ceramic discs with six-piston clampers up front and four-piston calipers at the back. The brakes feature enhanced cooling via newly designed ducts around each wheel. This is necessary to cope with the extreme heat that could be generated by the brakes.</p>\n<p>No interior photos have been revealed yet, but drivers will get a stripped-back cabin that&#8217;s devoid of all the &#8220;nice-to-haves.&#8221; Even the carpets and storage compartments have been removed. Like a true race car, the driver is seated in the middle, cosseted by a new carbon-fibre racing seat with a six-point harness. A left-side passenger seat is available, too. </p>\n<p>Elsewhere, there&#8217;s a F1-style rectangular carbon-fibre steering wheel and a model specific instrument panel, offering details such as track lap times, G-forces, as well as essential vehicle and engine data.</p>\n\n<a href='https://paultan.org/2020/08/05/gma-t-50-model-kelahiran-semula-mclaren-f1-enjin-v12-na-3-9-liter-dengan-jeritan-12100-rpm-rm13-juta/2021-gordon-murray-automotive-t-50-supercar-interior-22/'><img width=\"108\" height=\"108\" src=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/08/2021-Gordon-Murray-Automotive-T.50-Supercar-Interior-6_BM-108x108.jpg\" class=\"attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/08/2021-Gordon-Murray-Automotive-T.50-Supercar-Interior-6_BM-108x108.jpg 108w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/08/2021-Gordon-Murray-Automotive-T.50-Supercar-Interior-6_BM-70x70.jpg 70w, width=\"108\" height=\"108\" src=\"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/08/2021-Gordon-Murray-Automotive-T.50-Supercar-Interior-1_BM-108x108.jpg\" class=\"attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/08/2021-Gordon-Murray-Automotive-T.50-Supercar-Interior-1_BM-108x108.jpg 108w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/08/2021-Gordon-Murray-Automotive-T.50-Supercar-Interior-1_BM-70x70.jpg 70w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/08/2021-Gordon-Murray-Automotive-T.50-Supercar-Interior-1_BM-160x160.jpg 160w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/08/2021-Gordon-Murray-Automotive-T.50-Supercar-Interior-1_BM-216x216.jpg 216w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 108px) 100vw, 108px\" /></a>\n\n<p>Each customer of the T.50s will get the full &#8220;Trackspeed&#8221; individualisation package which includes set-up, training, racing and support. They also get to choose their colour scheme and liveries, fine-tune the suspension and seating position, and much more.</p>\n<p>“I’d like to organise a series of racing events as part of our Trackspeed package to ensure the T.50s is driven regularly by owners. There will be nothing like the experience of driving this car. And hearing it… well, that will be something else! I’d like each of the 25 cars to be completely unique from set-up to paint finish,” Murray noted. Production of the 25 racing T.50s cars will begin in Q1 2023.</p>\n<p><strong>GALLERY: 2020 GMA T.50</strong> \n<a href='https://paultan.org/2020/08/05/gma-t-50-debuts-true-mclaren-f1-successor-with-3-9l-na-v12-12100-rpm-redline-986-kg-rm13-million/2021-gordon-murray-automotive-t-50-supercar-exterior-2/'><img width=\"108\" height=\"108\" src=\"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/08/2021-Gordon-Murray-Automotive-T.50-Supercar-Exterior-1-108x108.jpg\" class=\"attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/08/2021-Gordon-Murray-Automotive-T.50-Supercar-Exterior-1-108x108.jpg 108w, href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/2020-nissan-almera-turbo-malaysian-model-has-the-highest-specification-levels-in-asean-says-etcm/nissan_almera_preview_malaysia-8/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1172144\"><img src=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_Preview_Malaysia-8-630x369.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"630\" height=\"369\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1172144\" http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_Preview_Malaysia-8-850x498.jpg 850w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" /></a></p>\n<p>During the product presentation at the <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/2020-nissan-almera-full-details-of-malaysian-spec-1-0-litre-turbo-3-variants-aeb-on-all-priced-from-rm8xk/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">2020 Nissan Almera Turbo</a> preview earlier today, Edaran Tan Chong Motor (ETCM) took the opportunity to highlight the high level of equipment and features on the model from the get-go. In what is a rarity but hopefully will become the norm, the company said that the Almera sold here has the highest specifications levels in the ASEAN market.</p>\n<p>It compared its top-of-the-line VLT variant with the range-leading VL sold in Thailand, the market that <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2019/11/15/2020-nissan-almera-makes-asean-debut-launched-in-thailand-1-0l-turbo-cvt-aeb-blind-spot-avm/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">debuted the second-gen N18 in the region</a>. By and large, the two versions are identical in terms of equipment levels, with items such as a semi-digital instrument display with a seven-inch colour screen and a Nissan Connect infotaiment system with eight-inch touchscreen display found on both cars.</p>\n<p>Likewise, the presence of Nissan Safety Shield 360 on both range-topping Malaysian and Thai models. The package features a raft of driver assistance components such as Intelligent Forward Collision Warning and Intelligent Forward Emergency Braking, which is also known as autonomous emergency braking (AEB), blind spot warning, rear cross-traffic alert and an Intelligent Around View Monitor (360-degree bird’s eye view) with moving object detection.</p>\n\n<a href='https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/2020-nissan-almera-full-details-of-malaysian-spec-1-0-litre-turbo-3-variants-aeb-on-all-priced-from-rm8xk/nissan_almera_vlt_preview_malaysia_int-42/'><img width=\"108\" height=\"108\" src=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VLT_Preview_Malaysia_Ext-14-108x108.jpg\" class=\"attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VLT_Preview_Malaysia_Ext-14-108x108.jpg 108w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VLT_Preview_Malaysia_Ext-14-70x70.jpg 70w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VLT_Preview_Malaysia_Ext-14-80x80.jpg 80w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VLT_Preview_Malaysia_Ext-14-160x160.jpg 160w, features not found on the <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2019/11/29/2019-thai-motor-expo-new-nissan-almera-1-0l-turbo/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Thai-market VL</a>, namely a cruise control system and 60:40 split foldable rear seats. The local car also has a higher level of equipment in a few areas, specifically in the form of its leather upholstery (fabric in Thailand), LED daytime running lights (halogens in Thailand) and its machined two-tone 16-inch alloy wheels (a size up from the 15-incher equipping the Thai VL model).</p>\n<p>As it is in Thailand, only a single engine option is available for the Almera, and that&#8217;s a HR10DET (designated the HRA0 in Thailand) 1.0 litre turbocharged three-cylinder petrol engine offering 100 PS at 5,000 rpm and 152 Nm of torque from 2,400 to 4,000 rpm. The mill is paired with an Xtronic CVT with D-Step Logic and Sport mode.</p>\n<p>Malaysia will have three variants of the Almera, a baseline VL grade, a mid-spec VLP and the aforementioned VLT. Bookings for the car open tomorrow (September 5), and estimated prices start at RM8x,xxx for the VL, RM8x,xxx for the mid-VLP model, and RM9x,xxx for the VLT. We&#8217;ve detailed all the specifications and equipment on all three Nissan Almera Turbo variants in our earlier post, which you can <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/2020-nissan-almera-full-details-of-malaysian-spec-1-0-litre-turbo-3-variants-aeb-on-all-priced-from-rm8xk/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">find here</a>. allowfullscreen></iframe></p>\n<p>Nissan distributor Edaran Tan Chong Motor (ETCM) dropped a veritable bombshell today by previewing the <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/2020-nissan-almera-full-details-of-malaysian-spec-1-0-litre-turbo-3-variants-aeb-on-all-priced-from-rm8xk/\">new Nissan Almera Turbo</a> to select media. We&#8217;ve already got a <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/2020-nissan-almera-full-details-of-malaysian-spec-1-0-litre-turbo-3-variants-aeb-on-all-priced-from-rm8xk/\">full report detailing the impressive specifications</a> of this B-segment sedan, but for those of you who prefer a video format, we&#8217;ve got you covered there as well, with a full walk-around tour and even our first test drive impressions.</p>\n<p>The new second-generation Almera is a step-change from its gawky predecessor. Based on the latest <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2017/03/31/all-new-nissan-march-arrives-in-the-uk-from-rm66k/\">European-market Micra hatchback</a>, it&#8217;s much longer, wider and lower than before, which makes a world of difference in making this car look more attractive. The bold V-motion grille, slim arrow-shaped head- and tail lights (both available with LED technology for the first time), sharp lines and floating roof all combine to make this a far more stylish machine, which bodes well considering the <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/video-honda-city-rs-i-mmd-hybrid-style-matters/\">fierce competition</a>.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s the same thing inside as well, with a much more modern-looking interior, the use of stitched soft-touch materials on higher-end models, an available part-digital instrument cluster, and an eight-inch OEM Nissan Connect infotainment touchscreen with Apple CarPlay connectivity.</p>\n<p>But by far the most impressive spec concerns safety. Not only does the Almera get six airbags and standard-fit stability control for the first time, but autonomous emergency braking also comes as standard across the entire range. For a perennial laggard like Nissan, this is a significant step forward, and it puts the ball in its competitors&#8217; court.</p>\n\n<a href='https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/2020-nissan-almera-full-details-of-malaysian-spec-1-0-litre-turbo-3-variants-aeb-on-all-priced-from-rm8xk/nissan_almera_vlt_preview_malaysia_ext-1/'><img Whichever variant you get, the Almera is powered by a new 1.0 litre turbocharged three-cylinder engine, producing 100 PS and 152 Nm of torque from 2,400 to 4,000 rpm. The car also ditches the ancient four-speed automatic transmission for an Xtronic CVT, which comes with D-Step Logic that mimics the performance of a multi-ratio automatic.</p>\n<p>No confirmed prices have been revealed just yet, but ETCM estimates that both the base VL and mid-range VLP will be priced around the RM80,000 region, while the range-topping VLT is expected to retail somewhere around the RM90,000 mark. Bookings are open starting tomorrow, so the launch shouldn&#8217;t be too far away.</p>\n<p>But enough of all that. You&#8217;re here for the video, so sit back and let our man Hafriz Shah get into finer detail on the car&#8217;s specs, as well as telling you what he thinks about how the new Almera drives. And as always, let us know what you think in the comments after the jump.</p>\n<p><strong>GALLERY: 2020 Nissan Almera Turbo VLT</strong>\n<a mage/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VL_Preview_Malaysia_Int-17-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx2/cdn36@2020_3/2020/09/05/08-56-59-705_b79fbd2d6a834c11.webp","http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VL_Preview_Malaysia_Int-18-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx1/cdn18@2020_5/2020/09/05/08-56-51-815_639fba8a75cbc631.webp","http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VL_Preview_Malaysia_Int-19-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx19/cdn43@2020_3/2020/09/05/08-56-59-699_8f7bdc47fa57d964.webp","http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VL_Preview_Malaysia_Int-20-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx32/cdn88@2020_4/2020/09/05/08-57-02-806_3776fabd37b97c09.webp","http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VL_Preview_Malaysia_Int-21-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx31/cdn11@2020_2/2020/09/05/08-56-52-921_efed2b7cf8f6bb79.webp"},"publishedOrCreatedDate":1599296207024},{"createdTime":"2020-09-05 16:56:47","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:56:47","title":"2020 Nissan Almera Turbo in Malaysia – 1.0 litre turbo CVT, AEB on all three variants, from RM8xk to RM9xk","link":"https://paultan.org/?p=1169913","description":"<p><a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/2020-nissan-almera-full-details-of-malaysian-spec-1-0-litre-turbo-3-variants-aeb-on-all-priced-from-rm8xk/nissan_almera_vlt_preview_malaysia_ext-2/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1171931\"><img src=\"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VLT_Preview_Malaysia_Ext-2-630x369.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"630\" height=\"369\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1171931\" srcset=\"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VLT_Preview_Malaysia_Ext-2-630x369.jpg 630w, sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Edaran Tan Chong Motor (ETCM) has officially revealed full specifications of the <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2019/04/13/2020-nissan-versa-revealed-almera/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">2020 Nissan Almera</a>, doing so at a special preview of the car earlier today. Although an official launch date has not been finalised, it is expected to go on sale in October. The order books for the car will open from tomorrow, September 5, and it will be previewed at selected Nissan showrooms nationwide over two weekends (September 5-6 and 11-13).</p>\n<p>We now know that the fourth-gen N18 &#8211; which made its <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2019/11/15/2020-nissan-almera-makes-asean-debut-launched-in-thailand-1-0l-turbo-cvt-aeb-blind-spot-avm/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">ASEAN debut</a> in Thailand last November &#8211; will officially be known as the Almera Turbo here. The car, which is locally-assembled, will be available in three variant forms. These are a baseline VL grade, a mid-spec VLP and a range-topping VLT, which were all shown at the preview.</p>\n<p>The estimated pricing for the variants were also revealed, but are indicative ballpark sums for now &#8211; that for the Almera VL is RM8x,xxx, and the VLP is also in the RM8x,xxx region, but expectedly on the higher end of the range. As for the Almera VLT, the range-topper will be priced in the RM9x,xxx zone. </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/2020-nissan-almera-full-details-of-malaysian-spec-1-0-litre-turbo-3-variants-aeb-on-all-priced-from-rm8xk/nissan_almera_vlp_preview_malaysia_ext-2/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1171748\"><img src=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VLP_Preview_Malaysia_Ext-2-630x369.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"630\" height=\"369\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1171748\" srcset=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VLP_Preview_Malaysia_Ext-2-630x369.jpg 630w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VLP_Preview_Malaysia_Ext-2-1200x703.jpg 1200w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VLP_Preview_Malaysia_Ext-2-850x498.jpg 850w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" /></a></p>\n<p>As it is <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2019/11/29/2019-thai-motor-expo-new-nissan-almera-1-0l-turbo/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">in Thailand</a>, all three variants will feature the same engine, and that’s a HR10DET (designated the HRA0 in Thailand) 1.0 litre turbocharged three-cylinder petrol engine offering 100 PS at 5,000 rpm and 152 Nm of torque from 2,400 to 4,000 rpm. The mill is paired with an Xtronic CVT with D-Step Logic and Sport mode, with power sent to the front wheels.</p>\n<p>The new Almera measures in at 4,495 mm long, 1,460 mm tall and 1,740 mm wide, and has a wheelbase of 2,620 mm. Kerb weights vary from 1,090 kg for the VL to 1,114 kg for the top-of-the-line VLT. Other relevant numbers include 482 litres of trunk space.</p>\n<p>Standard fit items across the range include Zero Gravity-inspired seats, keyless entry and push-start ignition, power folding side mirrors, tilt/telescopic steering wheel adjustment, a faux carbon-fibre pattern finish for the gear knob, front centre console with armrest, audio control buttons on the steering wheel, three USB ports and 60:40 split foldable rear seats.</p>\n<p>\n<a href='https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/2020-nissan-almera-full-details-of-malaysian-spec-1-0-litre-turbo-3-variants-aeb-on-all-priced-from-rm8xk/nissan_almera_vl_preview_malaysia_ext-7/'><img href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/06/19/spyshots-2020-nissan-almera-seen-once-more-in-kl/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">previous spyshots</a>, the Almera is fitted with LED tail lights and fog lamps across the model range, and the front lighting configuration also follows that as gleaned from the sightings of the car – the VL and VLP both come with halogen headlamps (auto on/off) and halogen daytime running lights and fog lamps. The VLT is the only variant to feature LEDs right through at the front (headlamps, DRLs and fogs).</p>\n<p>Elsewhere, all variants also come with a in-glass radio antenna and body-coloured rear diffuser, with the VLT getting an additional gloss-black trunk lid spoiler. As for wheels, two different designs are offered for the Almera. On the VL, this is a 15-inch alloy unit wrapped with 195/65 profile tyres. The VLP and VLT, meanwhile, ride on machined two-tone 16-inch wheels shod with 205/55 rubbers.</p>\n<p>In terms of specific kit, the VL gets front semi-bucket seats finished in fabric (with grey accents), manual air-conditioning, a four-speaker radio/USB audio system with auxiliary and Bluetooth connectivity as well as an urethane steering wheel.</p>\n\n<a href='https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/2020-nissan-almera-full-details-of-malaysian-spec-1-0-litre-turbo-3-variants-aeb-on-all-priced-from-rm8xk/nissan_almera_vlp_preview_malaysia_ext-19/'><img srcset=\"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VLT_Preview_Malaysia_Ext-27-108x108.jpg 108w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VLT_Preview_Malaysia_Ext-27-70x70.jpg 70w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VLT_Preview_Malaysia_Ext-27-80x80.jpg 80w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VLT_Preview_Malaysia_Ext-27-160x160.jpg 160w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VLT_Preview_Malaysia_Ext-27-216x216.jpg 216w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 108px) 100vw, 108px\" /></a>\n\n<p>The VLP increases the equipment levels to leather upholstery for the seats, auto air-conditioning and a dual-tone dashboard with a soft-touch instrument panel cover. There is also a six-speaker Nissan Connect Infotainment system with eight-inch touchscreen display and Apple CarPlay support, a leather steering wheel, a rear-camera and a full-colour seven-inch digital display on the instrument panel.</p>\n<p>The VLT features the same level of specification as the VLP, but adds on cruise control and additional driver assist equipment. It’s the only variant to feature an Intelligent Around View Monitor (360-degree bird’s eye view) with Moving Object Detection, blind spot warning and rear cross-traffic alert.</p>\n<p>Aside from that, the Almera is well equipped on the safety front across all three variants. The car comes with Vehicle Dynamic Control (VDC) and traction control, ABS, EBD, brake assist, two rear Isofix points as well as hill start assist.</p>\n\n<a href='https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/2020-nissan-almera-full-details-of-malaysian-spec-1-0-litre-turbo-3-variants-aeb-on-all-priced-from-rm8xk/nissan_almera_vlt_preview_malaysia_int-2/'><img Intelligent Forward Collision Warning and Intelligent Forward Emergency Braking, which is also known as autonomous emergency braking (AEB), on the entire Almera range, with even the base model getting it. As for airbag count, the VL comes with two, while the VLP and VLT get six (front, side and curtain). </p>\n<p>Six exterior colour options are available for the Almera, five metallic and one solid. The metallic shades are Radiant Red, Monarch Orange, Dark Metal Grey, Diamond Black and Tungsten Silver, while the single solid colour is Brilliant White. Elsewhere, the Almera comes with a five-year unlimited mileage warranty with five free maintenance service (parts and labour included). </p>\n<p>So there you have it, the full lowdown on the 2020 Nissan Almera Turbo from a specification point of view &#8211; all that&#8217;s left to reveal is the actual pricing and when it will officially go on sale. </p>\n<p>Here’s a detailed breakdown of the /image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VL_Preview_Malaysia_Int-3-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx19/cdn69@2020_4/2020/09/05/08-56-54-339_706c1a8ee84d821b.webp","http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VL_Preview_Malaysia_Int-4-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx33/cdn70@2020_1/2020/09/05/08-56-55-508_04f3bcbc2cc9fe8c.webp","http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VL_Preview_Malaysia_Int-5-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx10/cdn76@2020_2/2020/09/05/08-57-00-050_44beb897edfb5d00.webp","http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VL_Preview_Malaysia_Int-6-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx16/cdn25@2020_6/2020/09/05/08-56-50-625_531f441e30374ae7.webp","http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VL_Preview_Malaysia_Int-7-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx18/cdn16@2020_5/2020/09/05/08-57-01-856_c0f87d8141842887.webp","http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VL_Preview_Malaysia_Int-8-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx6/cdn95@2020_3/2020/09/05/08-57-02-811_393da4aa9bcba046.webp","http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VL_Preview_Malaysia_Int-9-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx13/cdn6@2020_4/2020/09/05/08-56-57-993_302a2d6eeb88d87c.webp","http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VL_Preview_Malaysia_Int-10-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx16/cdn57@2020_3/2020/09/05/08-57-23-793_5d1383eb46a207a4.webp","http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VL_Preview_Malaysia_Int-11-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx4/cdn15@2020_1/2020/09/05/08-56-59-334_75a570ae305e1bef.webp","http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VL_Preview_Malaysia_Int-12-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx13/cdn20@2020_4/2020/09/05/08-56-59-383_fddcf2f0a6b2d4c9.webp","http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VL_Preview_Malaysia_Int-14-108x108.jpg":null,"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VL_Preview_Malaysia_Int-15-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx13/cdn14@2020_6/2020/09/05/08-57-21-212_ea157a179b85f53d.webp","http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VL_Preview_Malaysia_Int-16-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx25/cdn13@2020_5/2020/09/05/08-56-51-771_9caccea001a8c566.webp","http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VL_Preview_Malaysia_Int-17-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx2/cdn36@2020_3/2020/09/05/08-56-59-705_b79fbd2d6a834c11.webp","http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VL_Preview_Malaysia_Int-18-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx1/cdn18@2020_5/2020/09/05/08-56-51-815_639fba8a75cbc631.webp","http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VL_Preview_Malaysia_Int-19-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx19/cdn43@2020_3/2020/09/05/08-56-59-699_8f7bdc47fa57d964.webp","http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VL_Preview_Malaysia_Int-20-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx32/cdn88@2020_4/2020/09/05/08-57-02-806_3776fabd37b97c09.webp","http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Nissan_Almera_VL_Preview_Malaysia_Int-21-108x108.jpg":"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/myreaderx31/cdn11@2020_2/2020/09/05/08-56-52-921_efed2b7cf8f6bb79.webp"},"publishedOrCreatedDate":1599296207025},{"createdTime":"2020-09-05 16:56:47","updatedTime":"2020-09-05 16:56:47","title":"Skoda Enyaq iV electric SUV revealed – up to 510 km of range, performance RS model with 302 hp, 460 Nm","link":"https://paultan.org/?p=1171610","description":"<p><a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/skoda-enyaq-iv-electric-suv-revealed-up-to-510-km-of-range-performance-rs-model-with-302-hp-460-nm/skoda-enyaq-iv-27/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1171791\"><img src=\"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Skoda-Enyaq-iV-27-e1599203625430-630x355.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"630\" height=\"355\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1171791\" srcset=\"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Skoda-Enyaq-iV-27-e1599203625430-630x354.jpg 630w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Skoda-Enyaq-iV-27-e1599203625430-1200x676.jpg 1200w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Skoda-Enyaq-iV-27-e1599203625430-850x479.jpg 850w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Volkswagen may be weeks away from unveiling the <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/08/28/volkswagen-id-4-low-aero-drag-crucial-to-efficiency/\">ID.4 electric SUV</a>, but Skoda has stolen a march on its parent company by debuting its version of the car first – the <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/08/12/2021-skoda-enyaq-iv-previewed-in-official-sketches/\">Enyaq iV</a>. This is the Czech carmaker&#8217;s first car to ride on the group&#8217;s Modular Electrification Toolkit (MEB) architecture, first seen on the <a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/06/15/volkswagen-id-3-deliveries-to-begin-in-early-september/\">ID.3 hatch</a>.</p>\n<p>Like the VW, the Skoda has a slightly cab-forward look, with a short front bonnet and overhang. The brand&#8217;s angular design language is on full display here – the front end is a riot of lines and facets, and the designers have pushed the closed-off octagonal grille further forwards. In keeping with the trend of illuminated grilles, upper trim levels get a Crystal Face which lights up the vertical slats with 130 LEDs.</p>\n<p>This grille works with the matrix LED headlights and the optional full-LED tail lights to perform an animated sequence when locking and unlocking the car. Along the side, the Enyaq keeps the upswept window line of the ID.4 but has a more pronounced shoulder crease linking the head- and tail lights. There are eight wheel options available, ranging from 18 to a whopping 21 inches in diameter.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/skoda-enyaq-iv-electric-suv-revealed-up-to-510-km-of-range-performance-rs-model-with-302-hp-460-nm/skoda-enyaq-iv-35/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1171800\"><img src=\"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Skoda-Enyaq-iV-35-e1599206570918-630x357.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"630\" height=\"357\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1171800\" srcset=\"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Skoda-Enyaq-iV-35-e1599206570918-630x357.jpg 630w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Skoda-Enyaq-iV-35-e1599206570918-1200x680.jpg 1200w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Skoda-Enyaq-iV-35-e1599206570918-210x120.jpg 210w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Skoda-Enyaq-iV-35-e1599206570918-850x481.jpg 850w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Inside, the Enyaq sports a very modern five-seater interior, consisting of a low-profile layered dashboard, a freestanding touchscreen, a slim 5.3-inch digital instrument display and a tall centre console with plenty of room to stow your belongings. The centre armrest hides a 6.2 litre Jumbo Box, while the compartment underneath the bridge-like centre console offers up another 11.4 litres of storage space.</p>\n<p>Skoda is offering various Design Selections with different looks and sustainable materials. The Lodge, for instance, uses an upholstery made from 40% wool and 60% polyester from recycled PET bottles, while the ecoSuite uses cognac-coloured leather treated using olive leaf extracts.</p>\n<p>As standard, the centre display measures 10 inches across but can be optioned up to a massive 13 inches. Based on the latest VW Modular Infotainment Matrix, it features wireless Apple CarPlay and Android Auto connectivity, as well as a Qi wireless charger. A touch slider eliminates the need for a physical volume control knob, and the system also recognises gesture controls.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/skoda-enyaq-iv-electric-suv-revealed-up-to-510-km-of-range-performance-rs-model-with-302-hp-460-nm/skoda-enyaq-iv-6/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1171770\"><img src=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Skoda-Enyaq-iV-6-630x420.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"630\" height=\"420\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1171770\" srcset=\"http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Skoda-Enyaq-iV-6-630x420.jpg 630w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Skoda-Enyaq-iV-6-1200x800.jpg 1200w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Skoda-Enyaq-iV-6-850x567.jpg 850w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" /></a></p>\n<p>It also features a new Laura voice control system which understands 15 languages, six of which come with natural speech recognition. The Skoda Connect app allows users to remotely control and schedule battery charging and the air-conditioning. Four speakers come as standard, with eight as an option; there&#8217;s also a Canton sound system with 12 speakers.</p>\n<p>Skoda continues to provide a range of &#8220;Simply Clever&#8221; features on the Enyaq. Underneath the boot floor is an adjustable storage compartment that also has room for a charging cable, which has a cap and can be cleaned using a cable cleaner. Without a fuel filler cap to speak of, the brand&#8217;s trademark ice scraper (with a tyre tread depth gauge) can now be found within the tailgate. An umbrella is also hidden in the driver&#8217;s door, just like on a Rolls-Royce.</p>\n<p>The Enyaq will be available with five powertrain variants. The base 50 model gets a rear-mounted electric motor that develops 109 kW (146 hp) and 220 Nm of torque, plus a 55 kWh lithium-ion battery that provides a range of up to 340 km. Opt for the 60 and the outputs are bumped up to 132 kW (177 hp) and 310 Nm, while the 62 kWh battery increases the range to 390 km.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/skoda-enyaq-iv-electric-suv-revealed-up-to-510-km-of-range-performance-rs-model-with-302-hp-460-nm/skoda-enyaq-iv-22/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1171786\"><img src=\"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Skoda-Enyaq-iV-22-630x420.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"630\" height=\"420\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1171786\" srcset=\"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Skoda-Enyaq-iV-22-630x420.jpg 630w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Skoda-Enyaq-iV-22-1200x800.jpg 1200w, http://s3.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Skoda-Enyaq-iV-22-850x567.jpg 850w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" /></a></p>\n<p>But it&#8217;s the 80 that delivers the most range, with the 82 kWh battery enabling the Enyaq to travel an impressive 510 km between charges; here, power is rated at 150 kW (201 hp). The two range-topping models use the same battery but add a second electric motor on the front axle, with the range dropping slightly to 460 km.</p>\n<p>The 80x increases the power output to 195 kW (261 hp), but the one you&#8217;ll really want is the performance RS model, which churns out a hefty 225 kW (302 hp). The latter gets from zero to 100 km/h in 6.2 seconds and has a top speed 20 km/h higher than the other models, at 180 km/h.</p>\n<p>All models are capable of 7.2 kW of AC charging and 50 kW of DC charging. The 60 increases maximum inputs to 11 kW for AC charging and 100 kW for DC charging, but only 80 variants and above get the full DC fast charging capability, with 150 kW of power.</p>\n\n<a href='https://paultan.org/2020/09/04/skoda-enyaq-iv-electric-suv-revealed-up-to-510-km-of-range-performance-rs-model-with-302-hp-460-nm/skoda-enyaq-iv-1/'><img width=\"108\" height=\"108\" src=\"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Skoda-Enyaq-iV-1-108x108.jpg\" class=\"attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Skoda-Enyaq-iV-1-108x108.jpg 108w, http://s1.paultan.org/image/2020/09/Skoda-Enyaq-iV-1-70x70.jpg 70w,
